Edmund Gilbert, for the murder of his apprentice, a charity boy; 


Edward Ryan, for stealing a silver tankard, the property of 


Dorothy Udall; 


Samuel Keep, for stealing eleven sheep and a ram, the property of 


Ann Carter; 


George Norton, for stealing one hundred yards of woollen cloth, the property of 


William Bray; 


Stephen Parson, for stealing a silver chocolate pot, a pair of silver snuffers, a pair of silver tea tongs, and a silver stock-buckle, the goods of 


Sir Simeon Stuart; 


Mary Cut and Come again, for assaulting and robbing 


Elizabeth Turner; 


Lettice Lynn, for breaking and entering the dwelling house of 


Matthew Wood; and 


Esther Fowler, for stealing various goods the property of 


Philip Shirley.
